>For example: x^2-y / 2x^2 + y^2 is said to be homogeneous as all  
>four terms (2)at the numerator and (2) at the denominator are of 
>degree two.
>
>But x^2 + 3xy + y^2 i'm told is also homogeneous in x and y. I dont 
